    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>QUEBEC PAPER MAKER EXPANDS SOUTH</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Domstar Inc, Canada's larest producer of specialty and fine papers, agrees to buy Ris Paper Co for $90 million in cash and stock (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Canada's largest producer of specialty and fine papers, Domtar Inc. of Montreal, has agreed to buy the Ris Paper Company, a distributor based in Florence, Ky., for $90 million in cash and stock. Raymond Royer, Domtar's president and chief executive, said the purchase would link Domtar more directly with end users in the United States, where almost half its sales are made.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
